---
layout: base.njk
title: Home
description: Mindful Engineering for software architecture, AI-assisted development, DevOps, Zen, and the human side of building systems.
---

<section class="hero-pond">
  <div id="koi-pond-container" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  <div class="hero-paper"></div>
  <div class="hero-content relative z-10 max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 sm:px-10 lg:px-16 min-h-[88vh] flex items-center">
    <div class="max-w-3xl py-24">
      <div class="eyebrow mb-8">Mindful Engineering</div>
      <h1 class="hero-title">
        Better software starts with<br>
        <span>better attention.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-copy">
        I am Roel van Bergen, a hands-on software engineer, coach, speaker, and Zen teacher exploring how teams can build software with more clarity, discipline, attention, and humanity in a faster, messier, AI-assisted world.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mt-10">
        <a href="/blog/" class="button-primary">Enter the writing garden</a>
        <a href="/work-with-me/" class="button-secondary">Explore working together</a>
      </div>
      <div class="pond-interaction">
        <p class="interaction-hint">Click or tap the pond to feed the koi.</p>
        <p class="interaction-count" data-interaction-count="feed" data-api-url="{{ interactions.apiUrl }}" aria-live="polite">
          <span data-count-value>0</span> mindful <span data-count-label>feedings</span> shared
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-24">
  <div class="section-intro">
    <div class="eyebrow">Start here</div>
    <h2>Mindful Engineering is software work practiced with attention.</h2>
    <p>It is not soft engineering and it is not vague spirituality. It is the discipline of seeing assumptions before they become defects, making trade-offs visible, creating feedback loops, and staying close enough to code to stay honest.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="pillar-grid mt-12">
    <article class="pillar-card pillar-engineering">
      <span class="pillar-number">01</span>
      <div>
        <p class="pillar-label">Architecture</p>
        <h3>Shared clarity</h3>
        <p>Architecture is not control from above. It is the practice of making choices, boundaries, and consequences visible so teams can move with confidence.</p>
      </div>
    </article>
    <article class="pillar-card pillar-coaching">
      <span class="pillar-number">02</span>
      <div>
        <p class="pillar-label">AI-assisted engineering</p>
        <h3>Deliberate acceleration</h3>
        <p>AI is a powerful mirror. It shows where context is missing, where verification is weak, and where engineering practice was too implicit.</p>
      </div>
    </article>
    <article class="pillar-card pillar-zen">
      <span class="pillar-number">03</span>
      <div>
        <p class="pillar-label">Human systems</p>
        <h3>Trust and attention</h3>
        <p>Software is built by people. Delivery, DevOps, leadership, feedback, and psychological safety shape technical outcomes every day.</p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>

  <blockquote class="thought-fragment mt-12">Software engineering is a practice of seeing clearly.</blockquote>
</section>

<section class="ink-section">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-24">
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-end md:justify-between gap-6 mb-12">
      <div class="section-intro section-intro-light">
        <div class="eyebrow">Field notes</div>
        <h2>Latest writing from the messy middle.</h2>
      </div>
      <a href="/blog/" class="text-link text-stone-300">View all {{ collections.post | length }} articles</a>
    </div>

    <div class="featured-post-grid">
      {%- for post in collections.post | reverse | head(3) -%}
      <article class="featured-post">
        <a href="{{ post.url }}" class="featured-image">
          <img src="{{ post.data.cover }}" alt="" loading="lazy">
        </a>
        <div class="featured-body">
          <div class="post-meta">
            <span>{{ post.data.pillar }}</span>
            <time datetime="{{ post.date | htmlDateString }}">{{ post.date | readableDate }}</time>
          </div>
          <h3><a href="{{ post.url }}">{{ post.data.title }}</a></h3>
          <p>{{ post.data.description }}</p>
          <a href="{{ post.url }}" class="text-link">Continue reading</a>
        </div>
      </article>
      {%- endfor -%}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-24">
  <div class="invitation-panel">
    <div>
      <div class="eyebrow mb-5">Speaking and collaboration</div>
      <h2>For teams navigating architecture, AI, delivery, and the human side of engineering.</h2>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p>I turn Mindful Engineering into practical talks, workshops, and reflective sessions that help engineering teams build shared clarity, make better decisions, and work together with confidence.</p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mt-7">
        <a href="/work-with-me/" class="button-primary">Work with me</a>
        <a href="{{ site.sessionize }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="button-secondary">View Sessionize</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script src="/assets/js/interactions.js"></script>
<script src="/assets/js/koi-pond.js"></script>
